; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures timer1 and generates a oneshot interrupt.
;
; B. Preparation
;    N/A
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. Timer1
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. Timer10 : PC6/PC6 (Output/Capture Input)
;               : PC5 (External Clock Input)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; Timer10
; 1. Channel                   : 0 (Timer10)
;
; 2. Clock                     : [ 0 p 0 3999 ]
;    Source                    : p (PCLK)
;    Source Divide             : 0 (Not available)
;    Timer1 Pre-Divide         : 3999 (Pre-Divide + 1)
;
; 3. Config                    : [ 0 i o h 10000 10000 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : o (One-Shot) 
;    Output Port Polarity      : h (High)
;    A Data                    : 10000
;    B Data                    : 10000
;
; Timer10
sendln 'cm timer1'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 0 p 0 3999'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i o h 10000 10000'
mpause 30
sendln 'log on'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 0'
